President Trump welcomed truckers and leaders from the trucking industry to the White House. He thanked them for their support on healthcare and acknowledged the challenges they face due to Obamacare. Trump expressed his commitment to repealing and replacing Obamacare and highlighted the negative impact it has had on the trucking industry. He also discussed his plans to improve the country's infrastructure, rewrite the tax code, and eliminate job-killing regulations. The President listened to the truckers' stories and encouraged them to share their experiences and thoughts.